        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-25 18:33:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> you will need the maven-stage if you need to produce maven artifacts\n> basically:\n> maven-stage: Signs jars and pushes them in an autorelease in Nexus2\n> maven-docker-stage: pulls any jar dependencies and build the docker images to push them into Nexus3 10003\n> \n> If you dont release jars (Nexus2) for these repos, then we can remove that job\n\nOk - so 2 jobs now. I would have to release maven-stage first. Once done, then I run maven-docker-stage to ensure it picks up the released artifacts from maven-stage?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
